          "body": "Paul's closing doxology is one of the densest sentences in the NT. It anchors three claims: (1) **God is able to establish** believers according to *my gospel and the preaching of Jesus Christ* — preservation is God's work; (2) the gospel is the **revelation of a mystery** — concealed for long ages, but *now manifested* through the writings of the prophets, by the command of the eternal God, *to all the nations*, *leading to the obedience of faith*; (3) **glory belongs forever** to the only wise God through Jesus Christ. Three time-zones: long-ages-past silence → *now* of manifestation → forever of glory. Two phrases bookend the letter: *obedience of faith* (16:26) is the exact phrase of 1:5, and *to all the nations* is the mission of 1:5 and 15:9-12. The doxology is Paul's deliberate inclusio, sealing the letter's argument and consigning it to the only One who can establish what He has revealed."
